  "identifier": "HB 586",
  "title": "AN ACT relating to health services for youths.",
  "abstract": "Amend KRS 156.502 to define \"medication\" and \"sunscreen\"; require local boards of education to adopt a policy authorizing students in kindergarten through grade 5 to carry and self administer sunscreen with parent permission and allow students in grades 6 to 12 to carry and self-administer sunscreen; require board policy to cover possession and use in various settings; amend KRS 194A.380 to define \"sunscreen\"; create a new section of KRS 194A.380 to 194A.383 to require youth camps to adopt a policy authorizing a child to carry and self-administer sunscreen.",
